Description:  This example creates an FCC single crystal using LAMMPS.

Prerequisites:  Install serial or parallel version of LAMMPS.

Usage:  ./lmp_serial < in.singlecrystal

Output:  Creates a dump file called dump.singlecrystal that contains the atomic coordinates 
	 of a 10x10x10 Angstrom^3 FCC crystal.

Contributing Author:  Michael Fortunato and James Larentzos

Notes:  See the appendix of ARL Technical Report ARL-TR-8213, 2017.

References:

1. Fortunato, D.E.; Mattson, J.; Taylor, D.E.; Larentzos, J.P.; Brennan, J.K.  
   "Pre- and Post-Processing Tools to Create and Characterize Particle-Based Composite Model Structures", 
   ARL Technical Report, ARL-TR-8213, 2017.